The paper deals with game semantics for first-order propositional logic, which is a topic related to logic and programming languages. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of advanced tools from game semantics, rewriting theory, and categorical algebra, which suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's title mentions causality, which could potentially relate to cs.LOgic (Logic and Verification).
